  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Restoring hope by building a free school, Cameroon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In northern Cameroon, children are mostly affected by poverty, malnutrition and lack of schools within a radius of 200 km. To cope with this serious situation, in 2017 FOH supported the construction of a free primary school in northern Cameroon by setting up 3 classrooms that allowed 70 schoolchildren from 4 to 8 years old to be accommodated. In addition to the Cameroonian National Education Program, English and Arabic classes are taught to students from the preparatory class.</narrative>
  </description>
